properties.propertyDescription: Identifier of the calendar
Title of the calendar
Description of the calendar
Geographic location of the calendar as free-form text
The time zone of the calendar. (Formatted as an IANA Time Zone Database name, e.g. "Europe/Zurich".)
Opaque identifier of the event

Status of the event. Optional. Possible values are:

    "confirmed" - The event is confirmed. This is the default status.
    "tentative" - The event is tentatively confirmed.
    "cancelled" - The event is cancelled.
An absolute link to this event in the Google Calendar Web UI
Title of the event
Description of the event
Geographic location of the event as free-form text
The color of the event. This is an ID referring to an entry in the event section of the colors definition
Whether the endTime is unspecified

List of RRULE, EXRULE, RDATE and EXDATE lines for a recurring event, as specified in RFC5545. Note that DTSTART and DTEND lines are not allowed in this field; event start and end times are specified in the start and end fields. This field is omitted for single events or instances of recurring events
For an instance of a recurring event, this is the id of the recurring event to which this instance belongs

Whether the event blocks time on the calendar. Optional. Possible values are:

    "opaque" - The event blocks time on the calendar. This is the default value.
    "transparent" - The event does not block time on the calendar

Visibility of the event. Optional. Possible values are:

    "default" - Uses the default visibility for events on the calendar. This is the default value.
    "public" - The event is public and event details are visible to all readers of the calendar.
    "private" - The event is private and only event attendees may view event details.
    "confidential" - The event is private. This value is provided for compatibility reasons
Event unique identifier as defined in RFC5545. It is used to uniquely identify events accross calendaring systems and must be supplied when importing events via the import method
Sequence number as per iCalendar

Whether attendees may have been omitted from the event's representation. When retrieving an event, this may be due to a restriction specified by the maxAttendee query parameter. When updating an event, this can be used to only update the participant's response
Extended properties of the event
An absolute link to the Google+ hangout associated with this event
Whether anyone can invite themselves to the event. Optional. The default is False
Whether attendees other than the organizer can invite others to the event. Optional. The default is True
Whether attendees other than the organizer can modify the event. Optional. The default is False
Whether attendees other than the organizer can see who the event's attendees are. Optional. The default is True
Whether this is a private event copy where changes are not shared with other copies on other calendars. Optional. Immutable. The default is False
Whether this is a locked event copy where no changes can be made to the main event fields "summary", "description", "location", "start", "end" or "recurrence". The default is False
Whether the default reminders of the calendar apply to the event.
URL of the source pointing to a resource. The URL scheme must be HTTP or HTTPS.
Title of the source; for example a title of a web page or an email subject.
The foreign id of the creator
The email address of the creator
The display name of the creator
Whether the creator corresponds to the calendar on which this copy of the event appears
The organizer id
The organizer email
The display name of the organizer
Whether the organizer corresponds to the calendar on which this copy of the event appears
The date
The datetime
The timezone
The id of the attendee
The email of the eattendee
Whether the attendee is an organizer
Whether the attendee corresponds to the calendar on which this copy of the event appears
Whether the attendee is a resource
The attendee's response status
Whether this is an optional attendee
Number of additional guests
The attendee's response comment
The type
The title

The gadget's display mode. Optional. Possible values are:

    "icon" - The gadget displays next to the event's title in the calendar view.
    "chip" - The gadget displays when the event is clicked.
The gadget's width in pixels. The width must be an integer greater than 0
The gadget's height in pixels. The height must be an integer greater than 0
The gadget's icon URL. The URL scheme must be HTTPS.
The gadget's URL. The URL scheme must be HTTPS.
Preferences

The method used by this reminder. Possible values are:

    "email" - Reminders are sent via email.
    "sms" - Reminders are sent via SMS. These are only available for Google Apps for Work, Education, and Government customers. Requests to set SMS reminders for other account types are ignored.
    "popup" - Reminders are sent via a UI popup.
Number of minutes before the start of the event when the reminder should trigger. Valid values are between 0 and 40320 (4 weeks in minutes).
